# API surface

Handlers live under app/server/api/. The HTTP method is encoded in the filename suffix: .get.ts, .post.ts, .patch.ts, .delete.ts. Paths mirror directories.

Examples (observed; not exhaustive):

- Auth and user
  - login.post.ts, logout.post.ts, change-password.post.ts
  - two-factor-auth.ts, verify-two-factor-auth.post.ts, disable-two-factor-auth.post.ts
  - mfa/email: send-code.post.ts, toggle.post.ts, verify.post.ts
  - mfa/passkey: auth-options.post.ts, register-options.post.ts, register-verify.post.ts, verify.post.ts, delete.post.ts
  - user.get.ts, user.post.ts, user/notification-settings.patch.ts, validate-token.ts
- Accounts and membership
