## Implementation guidance

- Use app/server/clients/prismaClient.ts for DB, redisClient.ts for Redis, queuesClient.ts for BullMQ
- Wrap with withErrorHandler.ts or call handleApiError.ts; normalize Plaid errors with plaidApiError.ts
- Validate inputs using Zod schemas where applicable (app/schema/zod.ts)
- Enforce auth via server/middleware/auth.ts and requireAdmin.ts for admin routes
- For long-running jobs, enqueue work (server/queues/*) and return a 202-style response pattern if appropriate

## Adding a new endpoint safely

1) Create the handler file in app/server/api/<path>.<method>.ts
2) Parse and validate request; authorize early
3) Delegate to a service in app/server/services/*
4) Add tests under app/server/api/__tests__
5) If consumed by UI, add a composable or store action, and wire to components/pages
